<HL>
   Forstmann Begins Tender Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
07/09/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   FST GRL
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
COMMUNICATIONS TECHNOLOGY (CMT)
</IN>
<LP>
   NEW YORK -- Forstmann Little &amp; Co. began its tender offer
for all shares outstanding of General Instrument Corp. at
$44.50 each, or a total of $1.42 billion.
   On Friday, in composite trading on the New York Stock
Exchange, General Instrument's common closed at $45.625, up
12.5 cents. Counting options that would be converted in the
purchase, the maker of cable-television equipment has more
than 32 million shares outstanding.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Forstmann's bid, scheduled to expire at 12:01 a.m. EDT
Aug.14, unless extended, is conditional, among other things,
on at least a majority of the shares outstanding, on a fully
diluted basis, being tendered.
</TEXT>
